07/10/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- President Georgi Parvanov starts a three-day official visit to Turkey on Tuesday (7 October). He is to meet with his Turkish counterpart, Ahmet Necdet Sezer, to discuss enhancing bilateral ties and economic co-operation. They will also discuss security issues, the post-war reconstruction of Iraq and further collaboration in the fight against organised crime and terrorism.
In other news, Bulgaria launched a project to establish a national information system aimed at boosting anti-crime efforts. The EU is providing 2m euros, while the government will provide an additional 2.4m euros. (BNT, bTV, Trud, 24 Chassa, Dnevnik - 07/10/03; BTA, BNT, Nova TV - 06/10/03)
